<p>During the years in which the show is set, Prohibition was in force in the States and cocktails like mint juleps became popular to disguise the taste of bootlegged spirits. </p>

<p>If formidable Aunt Polly, the matriarch of the Shelby clan (Helen McCrory), drank one she'd have given it a twist – this one has peach brandy.</p>

<p>For 1 glass – Preparation: 5 minutes</p>

<p>Place the mint and sugar in a cup and crush. Fill with crushed ice, add the whiskey and brandy, stir and garnish with fresh mint.</p>

